Package uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model

Provides the classes and interfaces of the MEKON Frames Model API (see uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon for general description).

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CAnnotatable
    Represents an entity that can be given a set of annotations when the model is loaded, which can be either some concept-level model-entity or the model itself.
    CEntity
    Represents a concept-level entity in the frames-based model.
    CFrameListener
    Listener for dynamic operations on a CFrame object.
    CIdentified
    Represents an entity in the Frames Model (FM) that is identified via a directly attached CIdentity object.
    CSourced
    Represents an entity in the Frames Model (FM) with a source-type represented via a directly attached CSource object.
    FEntity
    Represents an entity in the Frames Model (FM) (meta-level, concept-level or instance-level).
    IEntity
    Represents an instance-level entity in the frames-based model.
    IFrameListener
    Listener for dynamic operations on a IFrame object.
    IFrameProcessor
    Processor for IFrame objects.
    ISlotListener
    Listener for dynamic operations on a ISlot object.
    IValue
    Represents an entity that can be the value for an instance-level slot.
    MEntity
    Represents a meta-level entity in the frames-based model.

    Represents a set of annotations on some concept-level model-entity or on the model itself.

    Represents the editability from the client perspective of the instantiations of a particular CSlot.

    Abstract class whose extensions represent ordered lists of CIdentified objects.
    CIdentity
    Identifies a concept-level entity from the frames-based model via a unique identifier, and a label.
    CModel
    Represents a generic MEKON Frames Model (FM), within which domain concepts are represented by CFrame objects, and inter-concept relationships and concept-attributes by CSlot objects.
    CNumber
    Represents a numeric value-type, defined via a primitive Java Number type and specific numeric range.
    CSlot
    Represents a concept-level model-slot.
    CSlots
    Represents ordered list of concept-level model-slots.
    CSlotValues
    Represents an ordered set of "fixed" concept-level values for specific slots on a particular frame, instantiations of which are required for all instantiations of those slots.
    CString
    Represents a string value-type, which optionally may come with specific value constraints.
    CValue<V extends IValue>
    Represents an entity that can act as the value-type for an instance-level slot.
    CValues<T extends CValue<?>>
    Utility class that takes a Collection of CValue objects of a specific known type and produces either a List or Set of the relevant type.
    CValueVisitor
    Visitor for CValue objects.
    FIdentifiables<V>
    Abstract class whose extensions represent ordered lists, with element value-types that enable each value to be mapped to an associated CIdentity object, where that identity object can be retrieved via the value object itself.
    FSlots<S>
    Abstract class whose extensions represent ordered lists of concept-level or instance-level model-slots.
    FVisitor<A>
    Abstract base-class for visitors that visit entities from the Frames Model (FM).
    IDataValue
    Represents a data-type value.
    IFrame
    Represents an instance-level frame.
    INumber
    Represents a numeric-value, with the actual value being represented by a primitive Java Number value of some type.
    ISlot
    Represents an instance-level model-slot.
    ISlots
    Represents ordered list of instance-level model-slots.
    ISlotValues
    Represents ordered list of current values for an instance-level model-slot.
    ISlotValuesEditor
    Enables the editing of the current set of values for a specific instance-level model-slot.
    ISlotValuesVisitor
    Visitor for visiting the sets of current-values for specific ISlot objects.
    IString
    Represents a string-value, with the actual value being represented by a primitive Java String value.
    IUpdating
    Represents configuration for the types of update to be performed on instance-level frames as the result of reasoning.
    IValueVisitor
    Visitor for IValue objects.
    MFrame
    Represents a meta-level model-entity that defines a set of concept-level frames via a root concept-level frame.

  • Exception Summary

Package uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model Description

Provides the classes and interfaces of the MEKON Frames Model API (see uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon for general description). The main point-of-access for the client is CModel, which provides methods for accessing and instantiating the entities in the model.

NOTE: This is a companion package to the uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.motor package, with which it shares circular dependencies at the implementation level, though not at the API level. See uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon for further details.
